  "body": "#292 \r\n\r\nProblem/gap:\r\n\r\n- the repo already carries the compact D7 Yang-Mills theorem surface, but several public-facing summaries still read too generically and did not always say clearly that the Clay-facing claim is branch-scoped and axiomatic-construction-dependent;\r\n- the standalone Clay note did not name the imported compact-paper theorem surface in one place, which made it easier to misread it as a broader claim than the declared branch;\r\n- several chapter and synthesis summaries omitted branch-local qualifiers that explain why the four-dimensional form is curvature-squared on the stated branch.\r\n\r\nWhat this PR does:\r\n\r\n- tightens the standalone Clay note so its claim boundary distinguishes the imported four-dimensional form assumptions from the later repair-gap inputs, and names the compact paper's D7 Yang-Mills theorem surface explicitly;\r\n- tightens the compact paper's abstract, prioritized-achievement summary, and Clay/Jaffe-Witten relation paragraph so they state that the Clay-facing status turns on the support-visible continuum extraction plus Osterwalder-Schrader reconstruction on the declared branch;\r\n- aligns the README, observers/consensus summaries, and the relevant book chapter summaries with the same branch-scoped wording, including the ordinary reflection-positive vacuum and the no-extra-dimension-four-pure-gauge-operator clause where that qualifier matters.\r\n\r\nNet effect:\r\n\r\n- the standalone note no longer reads like an unconditional Clay solution outside the declared support-visible compact-gauge branch;\r\n- the compact paper now exposes the theorem surface that the standalone note is repackaging;\r\n- the public summaries keep the 2D heat-kernel bridge separate from the 4D Yang-Mills form and repair-gap theorem.\r\n\r\nFlag part 3: `funD4mentaL_phys1cs}`",
